# Security & token-budget rule

Detailed design: `references/design/07-security-and-tokens.md`. Hard requirements:

## Single secrets boundary
- Only the FastAPI orchestrator (`src/orchestrator/api.py`) loads `.env` and holds API keys.
- The OpenClaw skill (`skills/styleforge/`) and any NemoClaw-sandboxed agent call the orchestrator over `localhost:8000` — they MUST NOT load `.env` or hold secrets.
- The standalone CLI may load `.env` only for local tests/golden runs, never inside the sandbox.

## HTTP routes (CP-010)
- Validate `run_id` with regex `^[A-Za-z0-9_-]{1,64}$`.
- For file-serving routes, `name` must be a bare basename (reject `/`, `\`, `..`, leading `.`); resolve the final path and assert it is inside `runs/<run_id>/`. Reject on any escape.
- CORS: use `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` only; never `*`.
- Uploads: enforce `MAX_UPLOAD_MB`; validate the image by parsing with Pillow (not by extension).
- SSE event tailer: allowlist fields; never stream raw env or full user pasted text.

## Telegram & sandbox (CP-012)
- Bot drops messages from chats not in `TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_CHAT_IDS` before any GPU work.
- NemoClaw sandbox mounts no secret files; deny-by-default egress; verify with a blocked-host negative test.

## Token budget (CP-008 + CP-002 + CP-006)
- Enforce global caps: `MAX_TOTAL_VLM_CALLS` (25), `MAX_TOTAL_RENDERS` (20), `RUN_TIMEOUT_S` (600). On any cap, stop and assemble a partial kit.
- VLM `image_url.detail`: `high` for first critique, `low` for re-checks (attempt ≥ 2).
- Pre-resize images to ≤1024px long side before base64-encoding for the VLM.
- Art Director context is text-only — never pass image bytes into it; append only the failing asset's CriticResult; use per-asset `rewrite_prompt`, never a full manifest re-plan.
- `AssetSpec.flux_prompt` ≤ 600 chars, `negative_prompt` ≤ 300 chars (schema-enforced).

## Data egress
- Brief + reference image go to Stepfun VLM by design; on NIM failover, reasoning TEXT (never images) goes to NVIDIA cloud. Document this in `docs/deployment.md`. Provide `NO_CLOUD_VISION=1` degraded mode.
